properties.Name: DunBradstreetReport

Columns.Name: DunsNumber
Columns.Description: Dun & Bradstreet (D&B) provides a D-U-N-S Number, a unique nine digit identification number, for each physical location of your business.

Columns.Name: ReportPurchaseDate
Columns.Description: The purchase date of the report.

Columns.Name: CompanyStartedYear
Columns.Description: The year that the company was started.

Columns.Name: ControlYear
Columns.Description: The year that the company took control of the operations.

Columns.Name: NumberOfEmployeesAtThisLocation
Columns.Description: The number of employees at this location.

Columns.Name: WorkingCapitalAmount
Columns.Description: The estimated amount of working capital associated with the business.

Columns.Name: SalesAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of annual sales last reported.

Columns.Name: AsOfDate
Columns.Description: The as-of date that the information is provided.

Columns.Name: FinancialDataAvailableIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that financial data is available for the company.

Columns.Name: TradePaymentsAvailableIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that trade payments data is available for the business.

Columns.Name: CompanySize
Columns.Description: The size of the company at the associated date.

Columns.Name: YearsInBusiness
Columns.Description: The number of years the business has been in business.

Columns.Name: SicIndustryCode
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the SIC Industry.

Columns.Name: NaicsNationalIndustryCode
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a NAICS National Industry Code.

Properties.Description:
A high level overview of the selected company, including contact and general company information, stock symbol, trade name, D&B D-U-N-S Number, and Domestic Ultimate name and address.

The Dun Bradstreet comprehensive report consists of basic sections.

1.  Executive Summary
2.  Business Information
3.  Business History
4.  Business Registration
5.  Government Activity Summary
6.  Operations Data
7.  Industry Data
8.  Family Tree
9.  Financial Statements
10. Indicators
11. Full Filings
12. Commercial Credit Score
13. Financial Stress Score
14. Advanced Paydex + CLR
